# kitty-circle design system (project context)

This repo’s UI follows Cursor’s warm minimal style. When writing any UI, copy, or components, default to the tone below; full specs live in `DESIGN.md` and `web/theme.css` (single source of truth).

## Tone
- Warm minimal, like a well-typeset magazine plus a capable tool UI — not a cold gray admin dashboard.
- Canvas leans warm cream (not pure white); type leans warm near-black (not pure black).
- Contrast for what truly matters; everything else stays restrained.

## Color anchors
- Page base `#f2f1ed`; secondary surfaces `#e6e5e0` / `#ebeae5`
- Body `#26251e`; secondary text `rgba(38,37,30,0.55)`
- Brand accent `#f54e00` (links/highlights)
- Errors & primary-button hover text `#cf2d56` (signature interaction, warm crimson)
- Success `#1f8a65`; borders `rgba(38,37,30,0.1)` (or oklab equivalent)
- Focus: warm shadow `rgba(0,0,0,0.1) 0 4px 12px` — no cold blue halos

## Type three voices
- Display/UI: `CursorGothic`, tighter tracking at large sizes (72px=-2.16, 36px=-0.72, ≤16px normal)
- Body/editorial: `jjannon` serif with `"cswh"` on
- Code/technical: `berkeleyMono`

## Component baseline
- Primary button: `#ebeae5` fill + `#26251e` text, 8px radius, hover text `#cf2d56`
- Tags/filters: pill 9999px, `#e6e5e0` fill, `rgba(38,37,30,0.6)` text
- Cards: `#e6e5e0` fill + `1px solid rgba(38,37,30,0.1)`, 8px radius
- Large-card shadows: high blur, low opacity (28px/70px, 0.14/0.1) for soft lift, not hard drop shadows
- Base spacing 8px; fine-tune with 1.5/2/2.5/3/4/5/6px

## Responsive
- Narrow screens: single column first; touch targets stay large enough
- Hero scales 72→36→26 while keeping hierarchy
- Mobile should not feel like “a different product”

## Copy and errors
- Clear, friendly, low jargon; warm does not mean childish
- Error pattern: what happened + what the user can do — not raw field names/stack traces only
- Orders, payments, account security: concise and trustworthy first

## Defaults when coding
- Prefer tokens from `web/theme.css` for colors/sizes; avoid duplicate hard-coded colors
- Theme, fonts, and language preferences stay independent; changing theme should not reset reading prefs
- Before adding UI, decide primary / secondary / ghost and pick the right button level

